        "As a man of distinction, you understand the power of a well-curated wardrobe that exudes sophistication and refined taste.\nBritish Old Money style is the epitome of classic elegance, allowing you to showcase your status and success easily.\nAs expert stylists with over two decades of experience, we’re here to guide you through the most iconic British brands associated with the upper echelons of society for generations.\n\nQuintessential British Old Money Brands\nBritish Old Money Brands have a rich history, often dating back to the 19th and early 20th centuries when they were established as go-to labels for the aristocracy and upper classes.\nThese brands are synonymous with quality, craftsmanship, and a distinct air of “Britishness” that sets them apart.\nBarbour\n\nFounded in 1894, Barbour is a British luxury fashion brand renowned for its iconic waxed jackets and country-inspired clothing.\nThe brand’s classic outerwear is a staple in the wardrobes of many upper-class Brits.\nBest for\nWaxed jackets, quilted jackets, tweed caps, and tattersall shirts\nFormality level\nCasual to smart-casual\nBurberry\n\nEstablished in 1856, Burberry is famous for its trench coats, cashmere scarves, and distinctive check pattern.\nThe brand embodies British sophistication and is a favorite among Sloane Rangers.\nBest for\nTrench coats, cashmere scarves, tailored suits, and check-patterned accessories\nFormality level\nSmart-casual to formal\nHunter\n\nHunter, founded in 1856, is best known for its durable, stylish rubber boots.\nHunter boots are a must-have for any Sloane Ranger navigating the British countryside or city streets in inclement weather.\nBest for\nWellington boots, waterproof jackets, and packable ponchos\nFormality level\nCasual\n\nAquascutum\n\nAquascutum, established in 1851, is another iconic British brand known for its trench coats and tailored outerwear.\nThe British royal family and the upper classes favor the brand’s unique creations.\nBest for\nTrench coats, wool overcoats, suits, and polo shirts\nFormality level\nSmart-casual to formal\nTurnbull & Asser\n\nTurnbull & Asser, founded in 1885, is a prestigious British shirtmaker and clothier.\nThe brand is known for its bespoke and ready-to-wear shirts, as well as its ties and pocket squares.\nBest for\nDress shirts, silk ties, pocket squares, and cufflinks\nFormality level\nBusiness-casual to formal\nGieves & Hawkes\n\nGieves & Hawkes, established in 1771, is one of the oldest bespoke tailoring companies in the world.\nThe brand, headquartered at No. 1 Savile Row, London, is known for its exceptional quality and craftsmanship.\nBest for\nBespoke and ready-to-wear suits, tuxedos, and overcoats\nFormality level\nFormal\nChurch’s\n\nChurch’s, founded in 1873, is a high-end English footwear manufacturer.\nThe brand is known for its superior quality leather dress shoes, particularly its Oxford and brogue styles.\nBest for\nOxford shoes, brogues, loafers, and leather boots\nFormality level\nSmart-casual to formal\n\nSmythson\n\nEstablished in 1887, Smythson is a British luxury stationery and leather goods brand.\nThe brand is known for its high-quality writing paper, leather diaries, and accessories.\nBest for\nLeather wallets, card holders, briefcases, and writing accessories\nFormality level\nBusiness-casual to formal\nSwaine Adeney Brigg\n\nSwaine Adeney Brigg, founded in 1750, is a British manufacturer of luxury leather goods and umbrellas.\nThe brand is known for its handcrafted umbrellas, attaché cases, and travel accessories.\nBest for\nUmbrellas, attaché cases, briefcases, and leather travel accessories\nFormality level\nBusiness-casual to formal\nLock & Co. Hatters\n\nLock & Co. Hatters, established in 1676, is the world’s oldest hat shop.\nThe brand is known for its high-quality, handcrafted hats, including bowlers, top hats, and tweed caps.\nBest for\nBowler hats, top hats, tweed caps, and Panama hats\nFormality level\nSmart-casual to formal\n\nStyle British Old Money with The VOU\nReady to embrace the timeless appeal of the “Sloane Ranger” aesthetic and elevate your personal style to new heights?\nThe VOU’s expert styling packages for men can help you curate a wardrobe filled with the finest British Old Money Brands, ensuring you look and feel your best.\nInvest in yourself and your image – book a consultation with our experienced stylists today and take the first step towards a more polished, confident you.\nYour journey to timeless British elegance starts here.",
