      content:
        "The Sloane Ranger style is a characteristic way of dressing of the affluent British upper class of the 1980s residing in the fashionable neighbourhood of Sloane Square in London, UK. The term &#8220;Sloane Ranger&#8221; was coined by the British writers Peter York and Ann Barr in their 1982 book &#8220;The Official Sloane Ranger Handbook,&#8221; which [&#8230;]",
